    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="26"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d26">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/3160: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vincent</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-20">March 20,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received March 20—10:19 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>409. <hi rend="italic">Ta Kung Pao</hi> editorially comments that Japanese
                    rendition of concessions to Nanking puppet régime is smoke screen in war of
                    thoughts against Chinese people in occupied areas; that Japan aims at false
                    independence for puppets in order to bewilder Chinese people for further
                    economic exploitation through puppet régime; that Japan no longer needs
                    concessions since all occupied China is under her control and that signing of
                    agreement at Nanking by Tojo for return of concessions is but another expression
                    of Japanese policy in China aiming at complete control of continent through
                    puppets.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Vincent</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
